 Carlos Toro , 66 , worked as a mid-level member of the Medellin Cartel in the 1980s when a confrontation with his boss caused him to flee from Colombia fearing for his life .
Toro came to the United States and eventually began working for the DEA as an informant .
He was n't paid for work , but was told he would be rewarded with US citizenship .
Toro is now technically living in the US illegally .